      "writtenOn": "2018-12-17T19:27:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this will crash if name is empty because len(nameParts) \u003d\u003d 0, and LastIndex returns -1. L46 protected from empty name. This code should be consistent with that. Either add a check here, or remove there.\n\nThis case is unrealistic though. Step name is required, so milo shouldn\u0027t see a step without a name.\nIMO this would be dead code, i.e. checks against unrealistic cases, like build.Builder \u003d\u003d nil. I think we can just document \"A valid BuildPage must have a valid Build proto\" which automatically implies all the rules documented in go/build.proto.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 98,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 98,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "0202fc5bd30cedc3cd942bd8e447901a8bfa1118",
