        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-17T20:19:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think it\u0027s that unrealistic.  The user can ask Milo to load any arbitrary build.proto by uploading one to logdog and pointing to it.  The difference between having this check and not having this check is the user thinking \"Milo is broken\" vs \"My build proto is broken\".\n\nIf b.Project is \"\", then it either won\u0027t crash Milo (since it\u0027s not a pointer), or will fail earlier in the chain.",
      "parentUuid": "eb0d8e18_f8428d85",
      "revId": "0202fc5bd30cedc3cd942bd8e447901a8bfa1118",
